messages.content:
Viotto comes upon the construction site he has visited before.

“Oh, Christ.” The man currently nailing down planks groans at your arrival.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Ah, a fine replacement for a park indeed. He despises this place... the smell of wood dust in the air, so ready to trigger a dust explosion should there be any electrostatic discharge. Viotto glances around at the power tools filling the air with their disgusting noise, powered by these disgusting people. They have no care for anyone but themselves and their own pockets.
Wafting his way over to the center of the construction site, he raises both of his hands magnanimously into the air. 
"Hello once again, people of this beautiful country! This work you do... it is the cornerstone of our society, isn't it? We humans, we take on this endeavor... of inching across the land provided to us by God, expanding and rebuilding our communities, putting our blood, sweat, and tears into these projects, purely for the sake of those around us! That you would construct these things that you may never use, it is the ultimate sign of selflessness. You fantastic people!"

Would you do the same of a firefighter, or any other first responder? Would you question them in the middle of a blazing building, as they fight through the smoke and rubble? I doubt it."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
As he peers down at the words, his expression hardens.
"It has been said that the problem with being yourself is that you've been given the responsibility for all your own flaws. Maybe I'm the one who said that, come to think of it. Ha! But perhaps it's the opposite. The people around you are the ones you are truly able to rely on for help, for correction. Isn't that what a community really is? Isn't that what people say? And I would have to agree... community is often where people as flawed as yourself can remind you of how *sick* you truly are."
Viotto stares off around the construction site, his eyes filled with rage. This is obviously also part of the rehearsed speech.
Suddenly, his gaze fix back on that lone worker.
"And yet, after all this time spent with those of your ilk, you still remain as fucking impenetrable as ever. Endless, endless reinforcement! And you gain nothing of it! And so I ask, is it not necessary to take a side path? Who else is around you all?!"
He sweeps a hand dramatically in front of him.
"Aha! None other than I, Entenmann! Everyone must leave their proverbial comfort zone, take advice from those better than them in any way they may find. You know, believing oneself to be perfect is the sign of delusion - and what do those delusions lead to?! Danger! Danger for those around you, for those you truly love and depend on! That danger we are so ill-prepared for, obsessed as we are with probability!"

messages.content: "Ah, a... hammer. Yes, a model G40 16-ounce oak claw, if I'm not mistaken..." It is not this, and Viotto knows nothing about hammers, but he assumes the worker will not fact-check him. "Every time that hammer strikes that nail, there is a chance, a rather *unavoidable* chance of it putting off a spark. And do you have any *godly* idea what a dust explosion is? I would put it as... well, you should simply imagine that in your hand you hold a *blowtorch*, and in front of you is the *world's largest block of C4.* This irresponsibility will get you as far as you might expect it to. I demand that you report to your supervisor for a rubber replacement, or I may have to use one of my *abundant* connections to get this place shut down. And you wouldn't want to be responsible for that, would you?" He flashes an approximation of an evil grin, and whips out a small, laminated card. He holds it in such a way that the worker cannot see what it says, but it is an American Veterinary Medical Association membership card.

Viotto stamps his cane down in an attempt to hold himself up, but his legs buckle beneath him anyways. The pain in his knees from proselytizing betrays him.
Defeated, he slips his notebook back into his left pocket and clutches the vial around his neck. "God, give me the strength to deal with this setback..." He briefly wonders what he thinks he's being set back from, but quickly casts aside the thought and releases the glass.
"I can deal with this... I can deal with this..." He attempts to slow his breathing before D'Alicia reaches him.

messages.content: Viotto can make his way back without much trouble. The path is clear.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
As he walks home, he contemplates his day so far. It was very productive! That worker seemed to really get his message, and he ended up with the pamphlet. I'm sure he can work things out, regardless of how abhorrent he may be from a moral standpoint. These ideas are just self-evident at a certain point.
He comes across his beautiful home. He steps over the doormat, through the front door, and smiles. There's nowhere he'd rather be. We all have to push ourselves sometimes, but having a place to come back to, a place where love resides, makes it all worthwhile. He finds his favorite chair, and leans back.
His spine hits the cold, metal wall. He adjusts the stack of flame retardant plastic sheeting he's sitting on, and half-closes the lid of the dumpster. He made it nearly an hour this time, he thinks. He still needs to go out and find something to fill his empty stomach, but for now, he can just... write.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: And maybe... rest a bit. He's bleary, and weary. Ha, a rhyme! How quaint.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

author.name: scipe

messages.content: "GOD FUCKING DAMN IT"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Viotto jumps to his feet, almost hitting his head against the lid. He re-adjusts his glasses a bit and pushes it open. "If you insist on being here at the most inopportune times, could you AT LEAST try to be a bit more delicate about it?!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He sighs. "Sorry, sorry, I don't mean to be rude. I was just taking a moment away from this h- uh, this strenuous world. You know it takes its toll on me sometimes."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He backs away. “That’s… alright. I know you value having some solitude. I’ve got the same sort of need.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm sure you do, Deltent."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "What can I help you with on this fiiiine morning? I do recall owing you a favor for that assistance earlier."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He pauses. "Well, if you're offering... I guess an answer. Even now I still don't understand, and I don't want to let my chance to know slip by. You were a big deal. I might have exaggerated how closely affiliated I was with you, but I sure as hell knew who Viotto Entenmann was. But you gave it all up. Why? Did you change your mind about it being the path for you?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto considers for a moment. "I'm just not quite sure what you mean by changing my path... my path has not changed in the s-slightest. I have gone from protecting the innocent to protecting the innocent, arguably in the same way as ever. Prevention is simply infinitely more important than response, and I've chosen to get my priorities straight. Fire doesn't put off smoke until it's already burning, you know..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I may not have a satisfying answer for you if I can't understand the question!" he chuckles.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He leans back against the inside of the dumpster. It calms him.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I guess I can understand. Even if I still can't ignore the feeling that something must've happened." Sheeval leans against a wall. "If you didn't wake up tomorrow, and you were conscious in an out of body experience for some time to take in this fact, would you be satisfied with the life you lived? ...A weird question, I'm sorry."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"An odd way to phrase a question about the afterlife. Regardless... I don't think this is a question I can ever truly answer. Can anyone? The point of judging our actions on this Earth is to change the way that we may act in the future. If that gets cut off, I have no idea how I would view the morality of things anymore. There's a finality that I don't have the virtue of at the moment. That's all I can say."
Viotto's eyes indicate a different answer. They're regretful.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Sheeval notices his expression, and is silent for a moment. "Yeah... as usual, you make your case well, even if I don't see it the same way. It's a hypothetical I think about a lot, the age I am. I still don't know if I've done enough to make my impact on the world a net positive. If what I'm doing even matters. It's just... I want to do *something*. I wish I could've decided on a purpose as committed as you have."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Unfortunately, Deltent, I have no idea what you do, or what your impact on the world is. I am in no place to reassure you, because the only thing I ever seem to see you do is follow me around. Did you *actually* work with me? I admit, my memory is going a bit, but not so much that I would forget a co-worker. I remember everything about that clinic, and I *do not* remember you."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: His regretful look becomes slightly more challenging.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Sheeval shrugs. "...Yeah, I was never really a fan of that story. It relies on you being forgetful, which is a little ridiculous. It was a lie. I was still at university during your heyday."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"I see. A con artist as well as an intermittent stalker. If I did not find solace in us being so close in social status and age, and indeed, former profession, I do not think I would be able to tolerate you. But it is admittedly a good pairing. Two old men, abandoned by the world around them. It makes me wonder how you ended up here, but I would never be so *prying* as to ask."
Viotto senses that he's becoming bitter again. He tries his hardest to reserve that for his speeches. He quickly changes the subject to make sure Sheeval doesn't respond to the accidentally implied question anyways. 
"Any interest in trying to find some food with me?" He assumes that Deltent is on *protection sociale*, so he doubts that he would accept.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "...Sure. Though I suppose while I clear the air I should admit I'm not actually completely destitute. Still homeless, but not without means. We can eat like, an actual meal, if you'd like."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto is drawing a blank. He has no idea if this is allowed under his system of ethics. After staring blankly at Sheeval for around 10 minutes, he slowly draws in a breath, and says "Sure."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Lead the way."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

author.name: v_entenmann

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Sheeval frowns. "This establishment isn't that great.... no sauce at all."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Fine dining indeed, Deltent. Remind me why you dragged me out here? Is there something you wished to accomplish, or were you simply taking pity on me for my lack of acquiescence to the government's handouts?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Whatever. Unless you have some objection, I'm taking my nuggets back home. This has been far too much stimulation for me. Tell McDonald to turn his lights down next time."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "No, you just... well, okay. It was nice. Stay safe." He waves.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto waves back, smiling broadly. The smile is hidden by the scarf that he's pulled back up.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He starts making his way back home, one more time. There is no longer a pressing need for food. He considers going to a park like he had originally planned, though... he has much more success there than at that blasted construction site.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Weighing it in his head, he decides that he has enough energy to give it a shot.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He arrives at the park. There's a few people there.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
He looks for a suitable place to stand, finding a nice patch of grass near the center. He sweeps his jacket around, sticks his hand out in front of him, and generally tries his hardest to be dramatic. His other hand appears from his pocket discreetly holding a scrap of paper, shoots forward, and just like at the construction site, he raises them with an energy of magnanimity.
"Tell me, folks!" he says loudly. "Can even one of you here spell out your own ideology?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He waits desperately for a response that he can use.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: There is a long gap before someone responds. "I consider myself a libertarian."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
An incredibly non-specific answer, and not even a solid political party in France. This is better than he could have hoped for. "Ah, I see. Such a specific answer, such a solid choice for a Frenchwoman! And yet, where does that specificity lie...? Tell me. Which way does this go for you; did you decide each and every moral quandary for yourself and just *happened* to land in a place where you can use such a unifying word on yourself? Or did you start from a place of identification with libertarianism, and their philosophies gradually convinced you, brought about change? I bet I can guess, judging by the sorry state of our political affairs."
He looks coldly at the people around him.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "We divide ourself into these... roles. It's quite fascinating, isn't it? You are a libertarian, I am a proselytizer, these people are bystanders, there are... doctors, police, firefighters, name anything. When asked to take preventative medicine, is our first thought 'this well never be important to me, because doctors exist to save me'? When we are told that locking our doors at night is a protective measure, do we say, 'the police will be there to save me when I get robbed'? The answer is obvious, and yet curious all the same."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "We humans... we're obsessed with... probability. What is the chance of something bad happening to me? How can I lower it? And you, as a, um, uh, a libertarian, you... well, you... prioritize freedom over danger... or... well..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He starts violently stumbling over his words as he attempts to personalize the speech. This is his least favorite part of doing Q&A segments.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Look, let me get... back on track... I..." He flips through his notes a bit.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Yes! Probability! We are so obsessed with probability, and yet, I believe it was Albert Einstein who once said, "God does not play dice with the universe". If God is in no position to obsess over these things, how can we be superior to Him? It's preposterous."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ((albert einstein officially represented in q&a lfgggg))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((i mean tap. but also this viotto q&a of course))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "People... they treat life as a 'mystery' to be 'solved.' And yet, does this not defeat itself?  There are two approaches to a situation, you could say. React as events occur, or anticipate them in advance. To turn a life into this game is… to take the latter option, and in some way mold it into something self-contained, something unfettered by whatever result it's trying to achieve. To figure out the cause of something… what is it for? To avoid danger. But that isn't how you avoid danger in the real world, by funneling yourself down the most narrow, singular expectation of what to avert. You do it by FEARING danger, whether your empty head considers it the *solution* or not! To miscalculate is to throw yourself off of the scent of preparation, and we humans are so prone to miscalculation that some would call it our defining characteristic. No… a fire doesn't put off smoke until after it's too late. When you view life in such ways, you must accept the fact that the clues are nothing more than tragedies themselves."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He thrusts his cane at the libertarian, his signature move.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Tell me, daughter of God. What would you do as the flames roared around you?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: The libertarian, having been designated as female, responds "I think there is no God. So your argument falls apart there, unfortunately." She does not respond to all ten other paragraphs she politely stood through.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto is a bit perturbed. "Allow me to reach my point, then. What I said earlier about roles... did you understand my meaning? When we are told we can take further preventative steps in fire safety, in electrical safety, it is too easy to think, 'this is what firefighters are for - SAVING me'. And yet, salvation is the *opposite of what your goal should be.* Salvation is something that inherently assumes that you have lost, that you have given up. Humans rely on those around them? Pah. Such a statement is one dreamed up by the deranged to push responsibility onto some blind scapegoat. Relying on others is deferral. And deferral is death. This is something every man must understand. Do you see my point? What would you use your freedom for if not this? True salvation is... the avoidance of the need for salvation. I'm sure a non-religious person such as yourself would have to agree, no?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Tell me this. If you didn't wake up tomorrow, and you were conscious in an out of body experience, would you be satisfied with the improvements you had made to the world around you? The ways in which you had prevented others from coming to harm by your own carelessness, your own obsession with roles, with deferral?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: She considers this for a moment. "I'd probably haunt some people."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Think, man. Think. Where is this? How could you end up here? You've been focusing on the wrong things. Snow. Snow is not French, you know that much about your own damn hometown. Logically, this would have to be the Alps or Pyrenees. There was theoretically enough travel time between your home and here, at least...

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: There's constant watch over most of the Alps, it's just the more popular tourist destination. Of course, they're so large that ruling them out entirely would be dumb, but it's a matter of probability. The Pyrenees seem marginally more likely, although the mechanics of moving me there were still questionable. An AT-802F fire extinguishing plane, and military equivalents, could make that journey in about 20 minutes, but something so loud would at the very least require a sedative. I don't feel particularly drugged, although in actuality, I can't tell what time it is, so it could have been hours since it was administered. Would there be a noticeable difference between a regular long sleep and that? I have no way of knowing, but it still seems impractical, if only because of the noise it'd require to open my dumpster lid. I know I'm a light sleeper. Gas? Would gas have worked? Expensive and inefficient, and hard to conceal, but it seems like a potential way to avoid any of the contradictions I've noticed. Still, though, how would they have known what dumpster I was in? I could have been random, but there was no way to know I was there at all, no concrete evidence of my passing. Was I being watched? No, my movements throughout the city were too erratic. I doubt it was possible without getting close. I would have to be targeted. Who would be able to track my location? Who would know what dumpster I ended up in? Who... who knows... what...

messages.content:
*Dear Viotto,*
*I truly have chosen the most inopportune time to feel enough regret. They already think your belongings have been checked, so this should get through.*

*You have been selected for a strange sort of experiment called The Antarctica Project. I’m sure those more directly involved will tell you plenty of details. I’ll fill you in on a few important bits of information, the type of stuff I believe they might leave out.*

*The purpose of The Antarctica Project… is not something I can tell you. My regret still does not outweigh the gratitude I feel towards those close to me, and to tell you this would be to trivialize this entire endeavor. In any case, it should not have any direct relevance to you or your safety.*

*Safety. You were always preoccupied with that in your own way, huh? I’m sure you already disposed of the device they provided you (you are going to freeze to death without that, Viotto, come on) Here’s my chance to pay you back. The location this project will take you to is crawling with foul creatures that know nothing but violence. This is distinct from the people who are there, though you couldn’t be blamed for mistaking the two. I believe the people in charge are sane enough to realize you are an old man, so you should probably have a bit more vitality and pep in your step when the project starts. Defend yourself if need be. Negotiate with those who can be reasoned with. Be creative, and don’t rule out any options for being impossible. Believe that you can make it out of this not only alive, but even better than you were before. Make perception reality.*

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
*…Live, Viotto. You’re a nutjob, but you deserve that much.*

*The place you will end up is called Arctica. It is a large island kingdom that exchanges the conveniences of our modern world for the ability to perform miracles of magic. I hope, even if you now think I’m insane, you still take everything before the part where I say magic is real to heart. The country is ruled by a man named Aodh Praxis.* [There are a handful of paragraphs relating to knowledge about the culture and layout of Arctica that you can reference in the future if need be.] *I would prefer if you kept this under wraps. Share what knowledge you want with others, but it would be bad for you if the wrong people found out specifically that you had this note.*

*I guess there are some things I can say about the ones in charge. It’s “ones”. They are probably going to try to mislead you into believing there is one enigmatic individual behind The Antarctica Project. This is completely absurd, and not true. The “mastermind”... there are a reasonable handful of people who you could call that. I’m among them, I guess. And countless more are indirectly responsible for the fact that this project is happening. It will be easier to understand as you go along, probably.*

*…I don’t think we will ever see each other again. One way or another. I feel the specter of death approaching.*

*As a young adult, I studied the brain, convinced that by learning about the “key element” that makes a person a person, I could help people in addition to merely making a living. I saw past the barbaric practices of the past and understood what a delicate thing a human was. I don’t know where I went wrong. It was supposed to be for the greater good. It was supposed to be safe. …Viotto. There is nothing worse than a life lived with nothing but the void of what you once had.*

*The Big Mac and chicken tenders were delicious. So to everybody, goodbye.*

*Yours truly,*
*Sheeval Deltent, M.D.*

messages.content:
Viotto blinks at the ceiling above him, trying to take in as much as he can. The stone reassures him, although... the existence of it does not. Le Havre does not have alleyways with ceilings. He thinks. He would have noticed, right?
He grabs at his somehow present cane and braces himself against the nearest wall, feeling it for texture. He assumes it would be inert stone, but judging by his inability to glean much from the dirt in his last location, a coal dust-saturated environment is still not out of the question. 
Oh, yeah. His last location. The... Pyrenees, right? God, what happened? Was there a cave-in, like what took the others? A mudslide? His head certainly hurt enough to back up either of those theories.

Whether it was him passing out, or him being temporarily surrounded by dirt, it was hard to judge how exactly he had moved. Of course, the hallway being here wasn't out of the ordinary at all, was it? Below an area with both pre-arranged tents and high-grade technology... ah, perhaps this is where the wires for that large device ran! But... oh god, if that were true... 
Viotto frantically looks around for any visible bits of wiring.

messages.content: Hm. This doesn't seem like a viable exit, now does it... getting too close would... uh, it would probably be dangerous. How far can people fall? Hm. It... probably wouldn't work. Is there anything off to the sides, anywhere for him to step?

messages.content: Hm. Well, I suppose that does explain the long drop. Although it doesn't seem to be too likely, judging by the sun outside, flying vessels are luckily very well-constructed as to be mostly unaffected by lightning strikes. That isn't to say we're in the clear... those... orbs... are still there, after all. But there is very little left to do here. Viotto settles down on the ground and pulls out his notebook nonchalantly.

messages.content: It is.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"Fear... I suppose that would be a good one for today, if I have the opportunity with those people from before. If they did end up here... hm... wait."
How was there a flying vessel below the Pyrenees? It had... completely slipped my mind. Where... was everyone else? Where was that young, impressionable girl, that normal man? Both of them so open... both of them so... where... did I pass out again? Is that what that blackness was? I was... transported? But, wait. I was also transported the first time. So, logically, this is the exact same situation! This must be the plane that was used to bring him to that god-forsaken snowscape in the first place, and now he was being taken back. It only makes sense. He must have... fulfilled his purpose. Whatever it was. Perhaps this secret *sociale* society felt the need for a fire safety expert, what with their damned canvas tents and scattered devices. And that... the... the poor animal. I don't even want to think about it.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “IDENTIFY YOURSELF.” A shrill voice behind him.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Hm. "Why?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He felt no need for theatrics today.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Oh, shush.” A different, softer voice, followed by the sound of metal clanging. A woman takes a seat next to Viotto. “Hello. I do not get visitors often.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
These people seemed in their natural element. Too comfortable. This was no construction site, or park, or mountain. They were not off balance, not distracted, and there seemed to be no hope of meeting them elsewhere before first impressions were established. There was nothing to accomplish, as far as Viotto was concerned. Although, one thing did occur to him.
"Would you happen to know where that light on the wall is coming from?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “The lights inside? I did not set them up myself, but it’s just rudimentary illumination magic, I believe.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Is that a brand?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “What’s a brand?” Turning towards you.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That... alright, where is the person who *did* set them up? Perhaps I could speak to someone more *qualified* than you, lady."

messages.content: Viotto scoffs. This conversation is going nowhere. "Well, who else is here? Just direct me to whoever is in charge of this plane. Captain, pilot, I don't care. I merely need to find a way back to solid ground."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No matter. There are all sorts of strange names in the world when it comes to foreign locales. Just... I don't understand what you meant by... not being subordinate to the higher-ups on the plane. What are you, a stowaway?" He chuckles.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "No. I am not a stowaway. This is my home. Aside from the sealed rooms, I wander through here as I please. I suppose I am subordinate to others on this plane, but I question both the relevance and your terminology there."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto raised his eyebrow in disgust. "What terminology might that be? Might I remind you that *you* are the one who said there are many people in charge of this plane. And I feel no need to explain my relevance to you, when I am the captive here."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

The robot, which I will call Fema through context, twitches on the ground. "SUPPORTS FAILING."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Viotto walks meanderingly away from Fema Tinnitus, looking for any other people. Preferably in an upwards direction. The people in charge always like to be at the top.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: There is no room to enter on the first or second floor. On the third, Viotto finds a room that vaguely resembles a lounge. There's a little machine sweeping the floor clean. It's still possible to move further up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: A lounge... Viotto looks at the position of the sun to approximate what time it is.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: It's probably around 3 pm?

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Hm. Not an ideal time for any highers-up to be lounging, but perhaps for a lunch break. He briefly peers inside.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: There's no human inside. There's like a minibar and some books, and a poster of some diagram on the wall.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He walks slightly closer and inspects the diagram, hoping it's a map of wherever he is.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: His hopes are met. This place has five floors. The first two are crossed out with a red x, and the third says lounge. The fourth says "Nexus", the fifth "R&D", and the roof is labelled with "Helm/Observation Deck".

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Ah, the roof, of course. His intuition was correct. He had plenty of experience avoiding the government, after all, so *finding* those in positions of power was a cinch.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He shuffles back out of the room, eyeing the books, and continues upward.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He passes by some rooms, and makes it to the roof. There is an assortment of flowers laid out surrounding a hunk of scrap metal, as well as another robot facing toward the horizon. There's some complicated looking machinery in a small room.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto gingerly picks up the flowers and flicks them over the side of the hull. The books were insulated; even if a fire had broken out, it would have been entirely contained and had no points of spread. But these are out in the open among machinery! Awful.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He strides over the the second suited person and taps his shoulder.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Perhaps these are the guards, but they would likely know the way to the captain. It's not as if he's trying to escape, or whatever they're supposedly preventing him from doing.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
The suited person rotates their head 180 degrees and gazes at Viotto.

"Why did you disturb the flowers?" Nerissa has shown up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Timitus, you have already proven yourself worthless. That is all I have to say on the matter." Viotto flicks at the man's helmet inquisitively, wondering why he turned it around without responding.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "You are a deeply unpleasant person. Do you intend to do nothing but rub your hands on everything in my home?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No. I would never think of entering your home in the first place." He looks bemusedly at Timigus and tries kicking the man to get his attention. Perhaps he's asleep in there.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
The man’s eyes flash a little.

She pauses. “…Were you sent here without consent, then?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I am unsure how this interaction has proceeded under the assumption that I am an invader, miss. Perhaps you could work on your internal logic a touch."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "You do not live here. I have never seen you before. And people tend to only enter here intentionally."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I believe it was once said that those obsessed with probability are the most ill-prepared for danger. To base an accusation of me on what 'tends' to happen... I have many insights into information gathering, if you ever wish to discuss such thing. As of now, you are the most ill-prepared person I have ever met."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Now, where is the captain? I won't ask a third time." He decides to leave the sleeping guard alone for now.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "There is no captain. The vessel pilots itself, though I can alter where it goes if I wish."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hm. Autopilot without a captain... I can't say I know much about such 'vessels', Timigus. Perhaps you could *enlighten* me on where it has been set to *go.*"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Up. It gathers fuel whenever it can, and ascends. Laterally, sometimes it has gone far to the west over the sea. Other times, like now, it simply stays around this end of the kingdom. It does not ever go further to the East than where it began." She pulls out a notebook. "I have charts, but there is not a discernable pattern."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto attempts to snatch the notebook out of her hand.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: She turns into gas, and reappears slightly further away. "Impolite." Then extends out her hand with the notebook in it. "You may look."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((wonder if she's homophobic))

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Hm. Viotto's eyes seem to have unfocused for a second, but either way, he was being offered the notebook.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He grabs it and flings it off into the great abyss.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Not even pausing to observe its trajectory, he looks around for that room with the machinery in it...

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
Viotto is knocked on his side by a sensation similar to that of being slapped on the face, if being slapped also caused all feeling in your cheek to quickly disappear due to frostbite.

"I am Nerissa Titinius. I am not Fema. I am not Titimus. I am not your plaything, or a subordinate of some delusion of yours. My father is dead. My mother is the one you just desecrated the grave of. I wait here for my one remaining parent to return." The temperature of the air lowers. "And to think such an absence tricked me into thinking any being of flesh and blood is worth my time. Get out."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Ah, cold... how wonderful. This sudden gust of wind may have knocked him over, but it was a great development for allowing him to safely approach the machinery. He pulls an electrical hazard sticker out of his pocket and peels off the back, attempting to place it.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ((ROLL DEXTERITY (vital action)))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: The sticker barely catches on, and then blows away in the wind.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He. Tries. Again.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ((Roll dexterity (again)))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: It's oriented a little lopsided, but it sticks.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Orientation matters little to Viotto. He steps back, satisfied.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
Hm. He hasn't come across anything else notable thus far, and according to Timagus, there was no captain aboard. This seemed to be some sort of survey vessel, at the very least. 
One thing does cross his mind, though. He ignored those books because of their lack of traversal methods, but... there was a minibar there, wasn't there? If alcohol was present... how could he have overlooked such a thing?! Idiot! He sprints back down to the lounge.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: The lounge is still there.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He starts to gather as much alcohol as he can manage, but quickly realizes how bad of an idea that would be. God, he's off his game today! He separates out what he's started, and begins throwing bottles off the edge of the ship one by one.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Well, I guess this doesn't particularly bug me. Those all taste abhorrent. I still don't know why you're still here." Her anger has gone back to idle curiosity at the marvel that is Viotto Entenmann.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He ignores her and continues.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Someone really unlucky is going to be hit on the head by a bottle today.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto intentionally tries to avoid thinking about any houses he could be hitting below. He has to weigh the future benefit of his existence and morality against the current harm he could be doing to any unfortunate animals down there.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "This isn't a war thing, right? I know those bottles are supposed to be flammable."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Exactly."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He finally throws the last bottle over the lip, his work complete, and... lounges.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: No thoughts occur to him. No machinery left, the ship explored. That scrap metal at the top should act as a lightning rod, if anything...

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Well, I don't think you succeeded. There's no fire down there. At least not yet. It's for the best. That would be bad."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I was pointing out the astuteness of your understanding of the flammability of liquor, not confirming that I'm a hellish warmonger. But I suppose I vastly overestimated your ability to gauge meaning. I'm sure the two are equally likely, hm?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I think you showed up here and started breaking things, at the least."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And, pray tell, *what* have I broken?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Those bottles down below no longer pose any danger to us. I would consider that a *fix.*"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "All I have done is provide security." He spreads his hands magnanimously, wondering if there's a chance at accomplishing something here after all.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He surreptitiously pulls out his notebook.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: She laughs. "Is that it? You thought there could be a *fire* here?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Exactly. You could say that I was afraid - I've been accused of it many times, after all. Fear… it's what drives us all forward. And yet, at the same time, it is what holds us back. At least, that is what we've been told our entire lives. But let me say… isn't holding yourself back another expression of progress? I have held us back from a reality in which those bottles... and these books, could have posed more threat than they were ever worth. Danger is an expression of halted progress. Fear... is not." He begins idly picking the books out of the shelf and whipping them off the edge behind him.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "It's simple to conflate the two, isn't it? Fear, and danger..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "The former is a reaction to the latter, after all. It's so easy to view that cause and effect, to view these as *parallèle* instead of *perpendiculaire*."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: The books freeze in midair. "No. You felt it before, didn't you? There is no fire strong enough to outpace me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "But no, I don't think such arrogance allows you to avoid the problems you, yourself, have caused. There is a meeting point... nay, a crossing of paths. Life is a game of avoiding such points, wouldn't you agree?" He continues throwing the books over his shoulder.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: She continues catching and throwing back the books, creating a beautiful cycle of futility. "Machinery was not always as glamorous as it is now. When I first saw them, I was terrified... moving figures that jolted unpredictably, that rolled the dice with every step for if they'd combust into flames. But I overcame them. I learned that they were simple things that could not hurt me, and I made it impossible for fire to touch me. This is my domain!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto is so appalled that he can't even stay on script. He takes a second to collect himself, then turns around, filled with as much faux rage as he can muster. "*Simple* things that *cannot hurt you?* Tell me, then. Go on! Explain to me every single fire hazard that a machine such as the one on the roof poses, and *exactly* what preventative measures are in place. Go on!!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "This depends on what you mean by machine on the roof. The corpse of Mamba poses no threat. I have not confirmed it with that material specifically, but any defunct metallic golems are incapable of spontaneously igniting. The cause of that is the energy that flows within them, which a hollow shell has none of. The lookout drone is a more curious case, one that theoretically could ignite, but this is not feasible in practice. Even without my interference, at our altitude, the outside temperature is significantly lower than it would be on the surface, and it never reaches the risk parameters for even older models of comparable scale. All that leaves is the controls for the ship itself. I've never taken them apart, since that would be a foolish idea, but they don't involve flammable energies at all. Every remaining surface is made of stone." She says all of this without pausing. "Do you want to know about the other floors?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto approaches the room, blank-eyed. But there is a sense of something coming over him. These odd misalignments, these coincidences. How could he be at the bottom of the stairs? He wasn't blind. He didn't misremember the time he spent walking up those stairs. He didn't hallucinate. He didn't hallucinate those lights as they floated, those books as they returned endlessly with no intervention from that woman. There was no elevator that instant, that motionless. He was not insane. I'm not insane. There's no placement. How was it done? In what way? At what point? For what purpose? There is no purpose here. I am not important. I am not important to the government. I am not important to anyone.

messages.content: Viotto holds up his food. "Do you know what this is, people of Fr- Arctica? It is a destroyed life, given form as fuel. There is an idea here, as there is an idea in everything... the idea of a cycle. The cycle of humanity... we create, break down, rebuild, consume, and then repeat. Cycles are a tenet of our existence, and yet; there is an undeniable truth - cycles were meant to be applied to environments, not to us! Humans seek one thing, truly: novelty. A repeating form, then, bears no truth at all! Cycles of violence, cycles of abuse, cycles of regret... these are things which stem from a lack of progress. And on the other hand, there are cycles of water, of innovation, of capitalism. In other words - human progress is an expression of moving cycles from internal to external! Nay, cycles are the very idea of *stability!* So then, what is our ultimate goal? To create a world which is... infinitely stable."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "When I bring destruction to mind, there is an ever-present symbology, is there not? Fire... to burn, to reduce to *ashes.* That is, as a counterpart, the expression of a broken *external cycle.* Fire reverts you to the past... to a time when humans lacked art, culture, animal domestication, everything important to us! Fighting back against that... preparing for that... it is genuinely the most human thing imaginable! Please, understand what I am saying!"

messages.content:
The man speaks on the topic of creating magically constructed regions of space, or "pocket dimensions", emphasizing the importance of sticking to traditions set by "Father Magic". You aren't sure if you'd be able to do this yourself just from the lecture, but the concepts he's talking about are pretty straightforward. It's about outlining only the necessities of the region, and allowing more specific information to only be determined upon someone actually experiencing that location, preventing the immediate burden of magical energy from being unmanageable.
After some time talking about this, he does a very abrupt shift to rambling about the souls of sentient beings and everyone is kind of caught off guard by this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto interrupts the teacher. "Can I learn about ice magic instead?" He looks around, expecting support from the perturbed students.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: There are some murmurs of agreement from the group, though your suggestion is oddly specific. He looks a little peeved. "What's your name, student?"

messages.content: "Viotto Entenmann."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Well, Mister, *Entenmann*, what do *you* know about ice magic?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, I would consider myself quite proficient... I have demonstrated my mastery many times in the past. But I was hoping you could instruct me on how to perform it across a larger *area...* along longer stretches of *time...* in other words, an upwards correction. I need more... power, like a high-voltage *machine.* Although perhaps you are not aware of what such a thing is, considering the backslid nature of your establishment, nay, your society..."

It’s a size comparable to what he’s done before, though not a very thick layer of ice. There’s some chuckling from others in the room. Literally the nightmare scenario.
“Well, okay. Do you have a prior formal education?” Solnit.

messages.content: “Hmm.” He shuts off the cavern space, pushing everyone in it back into the room proper. “Well, okay. I’m not particularly familiar with ice magic. I’ll note this for next class, I suppose. I’ve a meeting with Dextrum. Anything else before I go?” He looks around the room.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

“Wasn’t this class supposed to be three more hours?” One of the other students asks to the no longer present man.

messages.content: Ah well. "My dear man... as he himself says, I have many issues with Sol here. He claims to be a workable substitution for a magical instructor, and yet he spends half the lesson discussing something *clearly* unrelated to what anybody in the room cares about, he ridicules me, leaves early, and refuses to teach us anything at all! I demand an explanation. Where are your tax dollars going?"

messages.content:
"Well, Sol,"

*"...nit"*, Solnit mutters.

"I told you to familiarize yourself with the curriculum, indeed?"

"I did. I taught what was scheduled for the day. Not wanting to meddle with the plans of who I substitute for, I cleanly transitioned into elaborating on something she wasn't going to do herself."

"Hrm."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What does that even *mean?* You 'teach what is scheduled,' you 'don't want to meddle with the plans,' and yet you also elaborate on something she would not do?! Can you not go a single sentence without contradicting yourself in your disregard for standards, man!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"It was an unresolvable dilemma."

"Catch twenty two..." the larger man adds.

"Yes, exac-what? Anyway, I had to teach only what was given for the allotted time period, but what was given was clearly insufficient for how long the session had to last. I improvised, and called it quits when even that couldn't work."

"I don't know if you're cut out for this kind of work."

Solnit stares at him in a very angry manner.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"Look, Mr. Dextrum, I am willing to *attempt* anything you ask of me, but when it's something this abrupt--"

"Yes, yes, fine. It's disappointing, but I won't fire you over this. I'll just have to find someone else when the Academy is lacking in staff."

Solnit exhales.

"You could really do to learn about communicating your desires with others, Solnit."

Solnit tenses up and is bothered again.

messages.content: I slam the back of my hand against the glass. "How do you suppose you'll be held accountable at those gates? It'll certainly be more fair than whatever happens to me in here."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "If I can tell you one thing, it's this - the legal systems in this world give accountability to those who deserve none, and give none to those who deserve it. The fact that I gave you a chance at the one fair bit of judgment imaginable is the best I could ever do for you."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
She whimpers, then takes a slow breath inward. “…Yeah. There’s no justice out there. I’m not here to lecture about morality. The girl. Violetta. She’s…” Magnolia looks away. “…my daughter.”

“Just tell me you haven’t seen her, and I can leave you to your own devices. It was my first and only guess for why she’d fly to France without warning, but I’ll need to search harder than that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I can certainly tell you that I've met a small girl recently, likely using a pseudonym. One quite obsessed with me. Is that helpful?"

author.name: scipe

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Well now, how about you bail me out of here so that we might go find her? This precious daughter of yours."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I! I…” She quiets down. “I don’t have the money. Traveling here was already more than I can safely handle.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "If you've already overstepped your bounds, then help me get out of here. By any means necessary."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “What? I’m not breaking the law for you! I’m desperate, yes, but you… have nothing to offer. Just a half remembered alias of what could be anyone. Vorel Leonetta? The hell does that even mean?” She fiddles with her phone.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I have nothing to offer? What about a direct line to this Leonetta?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “If you can provide that… then yes. I’ll do everything in my power to help you.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Very well. I know for a fact that this girl has a specialized communication device of some sort, and I know exactly where to find one that can reach her from the other end. Get me out of here, and I will provide you that information."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “How can I possibly believe something that vague from a deadbeat vagrant?” She looks at her phone. “Voreverl… Leocot?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: v_entenmann

messages.content: "And yes, exactly. Voreverl Leocot. Do I need to repeat it for you?"

messages.content:
“You got the name wrong, you st…” Her eyes widen. “No fucking way. That’s her. I mean, it’s not Violetta, but that’s the girl from… that’s better than I could’ve imagined. Why would someone change their name to… no, that doesn’t matter. She’s in Italy, she could have met up with… ugh!”

Magnolia kicks the glass divider between you two, shattering it into pieces.

“Run.”

messages.content:
They do not have visible windows. “Good day, Ms. Smith, how w—“ Magnolia shoves Some Woman onto the ground and keeps running.
“I don’t suppose you have anywhere we can *go*?” She yells back.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “That was Entera’s — my maiden name! I took my husband’s!” She keeps running through doors. There’s not anyone actively chasing them, it seems like everyone is mostly just confused so far.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Hmph. I'm surprised she's even married. I would have assumed the father was a no-show, considering her conduct so far. If she could find somebody willing to stick around, the next question has to be what the character of this man could even be...

messages.content: A man at the front desk ineffectually yells. “Excuse me! You need to get checked out!” Magnolia leaves the building.

author.name: scipe

messages.content: H- I wave my cane at the receptionist ineffectually, and burst my way out of the building.
