messages.content: “Fuck, fuck, fuck. There are taxis in France, right?! Everywhere has them. Or an Uber?” She looks to the road. She’s slowed down a little from the outright sprint, but is still moving quite fast.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Of course. But I'm not getting in one, and neither are you if you have any sense."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Where are we headed?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Anywhere. And I don’t know if you’re aware, but the police *do* have cars.” She’s using her phone again.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
I move to knock the phone out of her hand, but reconsider. It seems like a poor time to have a reasoned debate.
"That's quite the appeal to authority, Magnolia. The police do something, so it must automatically be good? We must stoop to their level? No. This is a resounding no, and we have no time to consider otherwise. Let's go."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: I start walking down the sidewalk, attempting to look non-suspicious. My scarf flutters in the breeze.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Are you an idiot? Is this a bit? The police walk, too. Where does your ideological purity draw the line? We can’t outrun them forever on foot.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't know what ideology you think I have, but this has nothing to do with it. This is practicality. Why would we, in our escape from harbingers of death, enter the place where death is exponentially more likely? No, more than that, Magnolia. Why would we give them a surefire way to track us? Why would we, in essence, create a new form of identification for ourselves with whatever license plate, make, and model you wish to attach us to?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Arrogance."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I—“ She looks around. “Maybe they still haven’t caught on…? I would’ve been sure just the glass would’ve set off an alarm.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't think they expected somebody to break the glass so quickly that nobody would be around to see the process."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "One of the perks, I suppose."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I guess they don’t count on an escape plan as asinine as mine.” She’s slowed down some.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I suppose not! Now, please, for the love of God, tell me *where we are going.* Or even just some basis to make the decision myself! What is it that you want? Who were you conversing with on that phone? Are we to meet up with Voreverr? Any response at ALL would be welcome."

Awful. My aspirations of personal improvement... how can they mean anything when my reach is so worthless? No, I... there has to be a way. There must be some storage method, some transfer, hell, some method of remote use. This isn't a meaningless battle.

messages.content: "I had meant that I was relying on you for guidance on providing help. You take one statement on a single moment, and you think it applies to the entire concept of my existence?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "No, I was being overwhelmingly generous. And in return, I have one additional question. Have you ever heard of a place called Arctica?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“Arcti…ca? I… there’s Ant…” Her face loses some color for a moment, then she shakes her head. “Why the hell would you ask that? You’re going to get arrested again on your own, Viotto. Is that what you want? Was-Was this all to waste my time and make sure the people you left in squalor stayed there?” 

She crumples against the nearest wall.

“Well, you won. Mom lost. I’m at the midpoint of my life and I already have nobody left and nowhere to run. Congrats. I’ll drink to your victory. This country has good wine, right?” She scans the streets.

messages.content:
She takes a deep breath.
"In your heyday, you were quite well regarded for success in your professional life. You left your job behind, though whether your passion for it disappeared I cannot say. What I can say is that you fully detached yourself from the family you had created. This was not an act of kindness. There was no harm caused by your presence you were trying to make up for -- no harm she or you'd have been aware of, at least. Because of this, Entera was left in dire straits emotionally and financially. She was, to put it bluntly, unskilled beyond being a homemaker. From second hand accounts, I assume your views on women had a place in that outcome. Struggling to get by, she barely managed to raise me, and I... barely managed to raise another. Decades passed. You never did anything related to them again. It is from this that I conclude you never really felt anything for this group to begin with."

She turns to you. She just looks tired, by this point. "Have I erred somewhere in there?"

messages.content: "In the last sentence, perhaps. I loved your mother - that much is undeniable. We married and had a child, continuing my legacy... does that mean so little to you, as a mother yourself? And then, I re-evaluated my priorities, and that love faded. I'm sure you know how love can fade, given the absence of *your* husband... and child, for that matter."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Ah, Solnet! Viotto's good pal. "Would you mind helping me free of these metaphorical restraints, my man?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
He smiles. "That's the goal, yes." He turns over to the security personnel. "Is wanting knowledge truly a crime? It is the goal of us all to uncover the reality of the world; to ascend beyond the mere shadows people live among by default. Could you really put a price on this noblest of pursuits?"

"Yes."

He frowns. "Oh. I guess on a literal level, that's true, yes. How about this, then? I am wealthy and influential enough to make whatever offense you believe this man is guilty of irrelevant. I'm Virtos Dextrum, you know."

Security man rolls his eyes. "Fine. But if my boss gives me shit for this, that's getting redirected to you."

"I essentially am your boss, when you follow the chain of command."

Viotto is released from paralysis.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"Thank you, Virtos." He begins walking away for a moment, but hesitates.
"You're not... an aspect of the government, are you? Considering you claimed to be that man's boss..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He laughs. "Not in the way you're probably worrying about. But I won't deny a connection exists. We met in the royal palace, after all."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I am the Eastern Advisor. I, well, advise His Highness on certain manners, and act as a representative for the interests of the citizens under my associated territory. I spend much more of my time as a scientist these days, though, really."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Ice forms, but it's less an impenetrable barrier and more a fence that he hops with minor difficulty. "Viotto, what do you think you're going to be accomplishing? Your being able to attend that one class was a fluke, and due to Solnit's inadequacy, you got almost nothing out of even that. Are you content being able to make snowballs?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Don't speak of your inadequacy to me! I am content being able to do *magic.* That may seem to you as if it was nothing at all, but for me... it is a complete perspective shift. Perhaps you should keep the relativity of opinions like that in mind before you continue following me."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
He sighs. "I wanted to help you, Viotto. Not in some nonsense charity financial business. Honestly didn't even understand that would be a thing. I wanted to give you access to the core of this world, such that a greater understanding could be reached. A structure, such that you wouldn't be wandering around aimlessly for the rest of your mortal lifespan on this Arctica. But I won't force you. You can lead a horse to water, but you can't make him think." Virtos stops walking after you. 

"What kind of world, what form of catharsis do you think you'll find among the shadows? Good luck."

messages.content:
'Let's talk about victims. I was often considered one. Often told that what happened wasn't my fault. But what does not lying at fault mean to you? It means exactly one thing - that there is no negative incentive. Do you know how I would have been held accountable for what happened that day, what happened right in front of me? I simply… wouldn't have. I didn't know electrical hazards, I wasn't responsible for them. Because we get to act like we all have these distinct roles to play. That we can segment ourselves. That those segmentations, those people with the correct place to stand in, can be pointed at to absolve ourselves. Nobody told me to adjust my life. My clinic was up to code. I wasn't the architect, the electrician, the fireman. 
Victimhood is society letting you know that you're in the right place. The fact that I was the victim, not those who died… it was telling me that that fire… was another element of perfection. Those deaths were an aspect of perfection. Can I accept that? Can you?'

messages.content:
He comes back like five minutes later. 
"So. What's the deal with Alto Titinius? How is a figure so critical still one with such an unclear historical record? This is my specialization, and although I cannot provide a factually agreed answer, I will go over the mysteries that surround this man and his contributions to the field of magic. Does anyone in this room know about the tale of the three wise men?"
Everyone in this classroom seems a little sluggish.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Elemental magic is eventually relevant, yes. But this really isn't what this course is about, mister."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Then this course is worthless."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "You're welcome to leave. Maybe you'll outrun the people I told about the guy who committed fraud showing up again." He grins. "An unyielding sense of justice! That, class, is the force of will that drives all magic, according to early theory. Unless it's intuition."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Normally, I would understand the necessity of theory before practice, Mr. (he checks the blackboard) Jobs. But this is no theory at all! This is history! Is this a magic class, or a history class? Because anyone who comes to this room to learn about magic in practice not only has their needs failed in the short term, but their time wasted in the long!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Is magic a normal part of your society or *not?* We certainly don't have a separate course for 'history within the context of *air*' or 'history within the context of *women.*' A course built around 'history within the context of magic' is a needless separation from history proper! This is clearly a tax scheme."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
He pushes up his glasses, doing the anime thing. "The study of magic *is* the study of history. We don't know everything about the world. We know what worked beforehand. Sure, we can alter traditions; the weird period of considering users of magic ambiguous is long gone. But building on what is established is how any advances work. You want all of magic to be a *subset* of history? A unit covered for a week? If you're that uninterested in learning, I suggest getting your education at Pierce's."
A few of the guys chuckle at this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No. I wish for you to teach me magic."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Clearly I am *more* interesting in learning than you are in teaching."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "For all your fancy words, you merely cover up the fact that you cannot argue against this simple request."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I am. You're throwing a fit because the class you aren't in hasn't tailored itself immediately to your preferences. This is not a class for the use of conventional magic. It is the pursuit of uncovering deeper knowledge about how it works, such that future development may occur. You are akin to a plumber entering a construction site for a new building and asking where the pipes are."

messages.content: "Can you tell me more about this murder?"

author.name: v_entenmann

messages.content:
"This is my domain! I am not that machine!" Femata Magus.

"Yeah, but you can't stop us from talking." Diana. "A man named George Tanaka was killed. He went by a different name in public life for the sake of personal benefit, which caused a lot of misunderstanding."

John looks at her disdainfully. "...Yeah, she's telling the truth there."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((the George tanaka session is going GREAT))

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Well, I can't say that sounds familiar. What was the different name?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"Oku." John. "Both she and I knew this. I hid it from the investigation because I wanted to preserve the way George wanted things to be, as his friend. Diana did it for her own benefit--"

"I wasn't just being selfi--"

"and so we were both heavily suspected by the detective. Then we ended up here. Diana had an inkling of the fact that we would, but I was just looking for her."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "This sounds like quite the long and interesting story. And I have absolutely nothing better to do than listen. Would you be willing to pull up a seat and recount it for me? I have it on good authority that there's a bar nearby on this ship with a nice view."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
Femata Magus sighs. And walks in a specific direction, which John and Diana slowly follow, eventually leading to the bar.

"So... well, there was this detective. Fainda Shinjitsu. She's kind of the centerpoint of this whole story." John.

"There's no way that's her real name, probably." Diana.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

"Wait just a moment. That name... it sounds familiar."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:

John looks over the PDA. "I've never seen anything quite like this. But it's not impossible to figure out."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

"Uh, maybe. It depends on what the hell she's doing. I'm not sure she was ever..."

Femata, peering over John's shoulder, snatches the PDA and walks off.

"offi...cially... Hm. Uh, I'll get that back in just a second. She's a hoarder so there's no danger of it being lost. I don't know if Fainda's actually doing investigation still, or if she's a suspect herself."

“I’m in a similar boat.” Diana. “I need to outright change my identity, actually, lest I be killed. So that’s a thing to work on.”

messages.content:
Diana buries her face in her hands.

"Hah!" Nerissa laughs arrogantly. "It is glaringly obvious that you cannot curry the favor of anyone! You were alone the first time and you're alone again now! Reason? Proof? Is that what you call running in a dark tomb for hours at a time while I deftly procure the favor of a potent ally, imbecile? I do not need to feign politeness dealing with you!"

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And that's how you judge moral success? By how *potent* your allies are? Of course, I should have known that you would believe might makes right. We have the makings of a dictator right here, folks!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"Oh, please. I'm not cut out for it. The handwaving away accurate critique, the obsession with control, the utter inability to perceive ones environment and wisely act on it; you possess the perfect skillset for a role in modern bureaucracy! All you're missing is the people you can neglect for your worthless excuse for a career, but unfortunately, you can't even muster up anything to ruin!" She's freaking out a little.

"This is good, probably. We're communicating how we feel." Diana leans back with the pipe idly in her mouth, having run out of ideas.

Diana is also annoyed. "*Excuse* me? I'm *so* sorry that people are overvaluing my names *worth*, but it's because there are people who fucking know me. You have any idea how many bland white bread humans you're utterly indistinguishable from, John No-Last-Name-Given?"

"I see. The discourse is not merely bidirectional." Nerissa stares at this exchange.

messages.content:
The funny little robot Nerissa was originally seen with can be heard banging into the door from the outside.

"Oh, shut up." Nerissa grumbles, then brightens her expression. "I can attempt this. From where do you believe the hostility within your relationship springs forth?"

Diana stares at her like she just said something incomprehensible. "Wh... oh. You want to know the fucking truth? I'm tired of resigned politeness, alright?"

John interjects. "Wait, you don't have to--"

"The hostility is that John had sex with me and is mad that he did that."

His face turns red. "You know damn well I'm ruined because of that! You're already committed to filth, but--"

"You approached me, asshole! Don't act like I was pressuring you into anything, when what really--"

"Ohhhh here we go, taking the literal route to make me look bad, when you OBVIOUSLY were taking advantage of my naivete."

"We're the *same age*!"

"I'm young at heart!"

Nerissa nods. "Such childish behavior. How do I resolve this?"

"Oh? You decide to awaken when she is asleep? Quite ironic. *(Chuckles)*. I don't really know you, so maybe you don't deserve this."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She looks feminine enough.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Does a lamb trust the assurance of a wolf downplaying his brutality? I do not believe so."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That seems particularly irrelevant, *lamb.*"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "My brutality was not at play in anything I said."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Nor should you have any reason to suspect me of carrying any. Do you assume all strangers to be wolves?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Elderly, infirm wolves??"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: The younger person, who has now been perceived as female, shrugs. "I wasn't willing to count on the 'infirm' part. But I see now it is true that you are unlikely to be physically threatening." She(?) turns to Magnolia. "Perhaps restraining her would have been more advantageous. But I think I could use you as a method of bargaining if she becomes hostile."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And why would you be able to bargain a stranger against a stranger?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "She's the one who barged in here with you. Maybe you don't know her, but she certainly seems to know you."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"And tell me. If we 'barged in here', why would you assume that we were so close as to place the others' life above our own, as opposed to... oh, I don't know, enemies?"
"Your safety hardly seems assured at all. In fact - if she indeed does know me, one way or another, your safety would be *more* assured sending me off so that she would be forced to *follow,* by *leaving.* You have set yourself up for failure here, lamb."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Interesting. You switch rhetoric twice; once to the presupposition that you are antagonistic, and a second time to my claim you are not. It seems you hold no true beliefs beyond what can benefit you personally." She(?) jots down some notes in a small book. "Is this a general principle, or merely applicable to your relationship with her?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Can you point out where I pre-supposed my antagonism? I don't believe I ever did such a thing."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Gaslighting too. An interesting case study. She seems younger than you, though. I would presume a familial relationship before a romantic one." She(?) looks back up. "I apologize for your memory problems. I should have been more considerate of that possibility. You begun your earlier statement with the claim that I should assume your relationship was antagonistic."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...why would my relationship with her being antagonistic preclude me lacking antagonism towards you?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "It wouldn't. I didn't imply anything of the sort."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Then... what are you arguing? I have been consistent this whole time, and yet you claim inconsistency, switched rhetoric. I would like to respond fairly to such an attack on my legitimacy."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "I promise you, nothing I have said so far has been inconsistent with my personality or values."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "I'm not arguing anything. I'm stating the fact of your behavior. You bring up two contradictory hypotheticals in a row. It's a scattershot technique in hopes one of them achieves the result you desire." She(?) smiles. "Though I guess this disagreement is useful. Is this your typical approach, then? You quite craftily distract with feigned ignorance of what the semantics of the others accusation are, another method of avoiding committing to anything. I can respect it tremendously. That ability to hold conflicting possibilities in mind has served my career path well."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't care how it's served you. Explain your accusation, or release me. There is no third option."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ((I have that meeting now. be back in 30))

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "The first case is simpler. That you claim the two of you to be strangers before deciding that saying otherwise can act as more beneficial. The second involves the more subtle connotations of affiliation." ((bye btich))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You have completely misunderstood. I never claimed lack of affiliation *or* affiliation - I merely presented hypotheticals that covered every possible situation. One hypothetical assumed you believed us to be strangers, and the other assumed you believed us to be acquaintances. And in both, the correct solution is identical, so it prevents me from having to prove our relationship to you to make that point, something I would be eminently unable to do with her unconscious. If you believe that 'demonstrating overarching safety to a response' is somehow hypocrisy, then that surely says more about you than I. Projecting intent onto me is not somehow a reading of my character."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “It most certainly is. All readings of character are exactly that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do you believe yourself to be a blank slate? A being with no intent yourself?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Not particularly, no.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Then my statement holds."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Of course. I never claimed you were inconsistent logically. You are a rather adept communicator, and nothing you’ve said has been demonstrably false.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "The gaslighting accusation is not taken lightly, girl."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “What gaslighting accusation?” She(?) smiles.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Is that a poor attempt at a joke about gaslighting?"

author.name: v_entenmann

"You're in Barcelonnette [southeast france place], and this is a house I rented. I think that woman was under the impression it was unoccupied. She was shocked I was here. I have French heritage, so I've stayed here as a change of pace recently. I don't feel comfortable telling you my real name, but you may call me DA. It is the name I go by professionally as a writer. I'm not successful enough you'd know of anything I've done, though. Especially at your age. I don't think anyone above 30 has ever touched a visual novel." 

DA looks back at the computer. "If you really don't know that woman, her name is Magnolia Smith. She's labelled as wanted in the same listing as you."

Why is she here?
"The veterinarian's oath is... much more specific. It speaks not of patients, but of society. Not of avoiding harm, but of promoting wellness."

"It's also a proponent of medical research and resource conservation. Much more specific than anything you may have heard of the Hippocratic oath, surely!"

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It means, I don't keep a notarized index of my location at each minute for your sake."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Ok, but I'm not asking you for a time of day, I'm asking, like, was this months ago, years, just today?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Why are we even discussing this?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: A man's voice interrupts your conversation. "Halt! Identify yourselves."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Hmph. Do you wish to be 'smarmy'? I am not asking." This man is dressed in a suit. He doesn't look like law enforcement.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You just did ask."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Which is it, then?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Identify yourselves. This is my demand."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I will not submit to pressure from *suits*."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Magnolia nods. "Yeah, I don't really see a reason that we should care about anything you ask of us. You're clearly not a cop or something."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I did not ask." The man in the suit is insistent on this point.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Government, at the very least.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Likely a fed.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "You very eminently did. You've asked at least three times, in fact."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Are you suffering from short-term memory impairment?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He smirks.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "To ask implies a desire for knowledge one does not have, as well as the possibility that something beyond expectation will happen. Neither are the case for me. I know everything."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Magnolia buries her head in her hands. "I hate France so much."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Don't blame France for... whoever this is. A bit suspicious coming from the person who just accused another of racism, wouldn't you say??"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"The French aren't a race, they're just a nationality. Or like, a weird social club." Magnolia rolls her eyes.

"I'm actually not French." The man in the suit clarifies.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, and I'm sure that you'd object to, say, Islamophobia being called racism? Surely?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Riiiight?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"Yeah, that's a religion. You can be racist against Arabs, but that wouldn't be the right word for that."

The man in the suit attempts to redirect the topic. "This seems unrelated to anything."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm glad you're so consistent, *sweetheart.*"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "And what are your thoughts on reverse racism? Care to tell me about that one?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"Do not call me that." Magnolia glares.

"That is a term of endearment more commonly associated with romantic pairings. It would be inappropriate even under the best of circumstances." The man in the suit objects in his own way.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And why shouldn't I?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He implicitly ignores the fed.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
Magnolia implicitly ignores him. "Who are you, anyway? Maybe we'd answer the thing you did *ask* if you gave us any reason to."

The man in the suit thinks to himself for a moment. "Jay. Jay Orphaned. I'm here on official business."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That is a word, not a name."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “It is both. Have you read *The Great Gatsby*?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Of course."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Have you read 'To the Vanishing Point' by Alan Dean Foster?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Yes.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I do not see its relevance.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I think if you can't see its relevance, then you missed the entire point of the narrative..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “If you are attempting to reference it on a thematic level, I can understand a connection. But mine was much more literal. The titular character is named Jay. It is a real name.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I was referring to your last name. Orphan."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Orphaned. That is considerably less common, yes. But real words are commonly last names. Reaction. Moment. Many different colors double as surnames.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I've never heard of such a thing. Maybe it's a non-French occurrence. I'm sure you would be well versed in *those*."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He says this derogatorily, of course.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Yes, I would be.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Then what point could you possibly be making?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Point? My original point was an expression of my desire to have you introduce yourselves, but Viotto Entenmann is nothing if not stubborn. As anticipated, you did not. “

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "So your point was to waste time, then. A fitting pastime for the all-knowing."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “My point was to approximate a normal interaction as best I could.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That's exactly what I just said."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Do you consider that a waste of time?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Did it accomplish anything?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“I think it did. Consider a murderer on the loose asking you where a child he is planning to murder ran.”

“What are you two *fucking* talking about?” Magnolia interrupts.

Jay ignores her. “Even if you knew the answer, telling him would be an obscene extension of committing to honesty.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Telling who?!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “The hypothetical murderer. He is the one who asked you the question.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You're a murderer???"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "We should be going, Magnolia."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "This is a dangerous situation."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “What?! He’s obviously not a murderer. I mean, maybe he is, but nothing has implied that.” Magnolia stares at you, then at Jay.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I have never killed anyone.” Jay states this truthfully.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Aaaaaaagh!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: I hold my head in my hands.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Leave! Just leave!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I cannot leave. I am not the murderer, Viotto. I am the man deceiving the murderer.” The stoic man starts rushing through his words slightly.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Are you accusing ME of murder now?! Because your deception isn't working at all!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “You must have noticed a shift, right? After you had a near death experience from the wounds sustained via Bill Jobs?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You don't know everything! Nobody could know everything!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ~~What?~~

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Who the hell is Bill Jobs?!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ~~Oh, fuck no. “Jay Orphaned”? Real fucking funny.~~

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: The man puts his hand to his head in exasperation. “I’m trapped, and this was my last stand. I realized passivity would solve nothing, and that the stakes if I failed were far too grave.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Do you think the world you live in is real, Viotto?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You don't need to quote To the Vanishing Point for me to believe that you've read it, Jay."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“I see. You never answer a question. It’s no use delaying the conversation. Your answer doesn’t matter. Here’s what does.”
He clears his throat. “You pride yourself on your ability to learn and adapt. I have no need for such things, having reached the plateau I have, but there is value in that for you. Someone is going to crush your potential and everyone else’s.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I've answered every single question you've put before me, despite the apparent nonsense involved with doing so to a person who claims to know the responses in advance. Every single move you've made has been some ostensible delay. It's confounding that you could be so turned around about what's happening here."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“???????” Magnolia doesn’t understand what’s happening.

“Yes… I was never truly capable of predicting people with accuracy. Such complex ideologies are fascinating to me. I hope your journey encounters more, Viotto.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Perhaps this is all simply a case study on how disgusting humanity is truly capable of being…

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Claiming to know everything...

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: It's an affront to God Himself.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Viotto turns to Magnolia again. "We have no incentive to continue listening to the ramblings of a clown. Let's get out of here."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “No.” They don’t exit the area of influence of this man. “For as long as I can, I will try to find some way out. Through curiosity, independent investigation, there must be something. You will learn. Or one of the other participants will. They have to. Otherwise this… ridiculous farce, this chicanery, will have been meaningless.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Are you safe, Viotto? Is the world safe? I am asking you things now. I am endangering all of us by acknowledging my lack of certainty.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Who watches the one who watches us all?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "The mind is the mirror of the soul. If farces are all you see, then perhaps the meaning you're looking for has been in the rearview this whole time."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Do you think you are going to be able to preserve what is important to you via obstinance?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Suddenly, you can’t see that guy anymore. He’s gone and he’s never going to fucking show up again.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

As indicated, Magnolia turns a corner and comes running over.

She looks at you two. "Y... oh. Um. Thanks, Viotto. I'm sorry for snapping at you, before."

"What the hell are you thanking him for? You think this decrepit creep is the reason I stopped? I decided it wasn't worth it to keep going like this. Here I am, Magnolia. And I think I'm aware why you're here. So let's go ahead. What do these three generations want, huh? I want you both to fuck off."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:

"Don't talk about him like that, young lady!" Magnolia yells. "This is the girl I was looking for. My daughter. Violetta."

Violetta sighs. "...Quit saying it like that."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: v_entenmann

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Anyways, can you answer my question?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"I don't care about her anymore, no... she was just a means to--"

"Well I *do*." Violetta interjects. "I'd love nothing more than to meet with her."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm afraid I have a much more vested interest in helping your mother than you, so I think it's clear who we're defaulting to here."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "If we do decide to go that way, though, I'd like it to be noted that Rowen is meeting back up with her, apparently. So we need only to go with him to accomplish that goal."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "If not, I would *love* to meet your father!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Just to get a look at things.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: It's a bit disturbing that he- oh, wait, no, we were kidnapped, that's right. He doesn't bear the responsibility here. Or does he? I'm still very unclear on the details there. Where did Magnolia get kidnapped from, anyhow?

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"Who the hell is Rowen?" Violetta.

"Some guy." Magnolia answers half-heartedly.

"I didn't *ask* you." She turns to Viotto. "My father's dead. That's what gave her custody. But she has *no* grounds to harass me anymore. I'm an adult."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "*Are* you now. That's amazing. I'm so proud of you."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Viotto's thoughts on single motherhood are complex, of course, but Magnolia really is doing a fucking miserable job of it, isn't she.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He's really not sure what he can do about that, though.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: People are entitled to their flaws.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I don't care about your approval. I don't know what ideas she's given you, but the two of us share no familial relationship. I just know of you."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I doubt that."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "So, what is it going to be, Magnolia?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"I take my daughter back home. I don't know... it's going to be hard. Since I'm still a wanted felon in at least one country. But--"

"You're *what?*" Violetta. "I already wasn't going to go with you! You didn't need to also get yourself into jail! I mean, what, you want to fuckin' swim the Atlantic? They don't let people like this on planes!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((sorry, I was getting a snack))

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Magnolia, I think France would be safer for your daughter than that swim, or that plane ride. She's right."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "It would be helpful if she explained how exactly she got into this mess in the first place, though, and what's stopping it from just repeating itself." He shoots Violetta a pointed look.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"There is no '*mess*'. I decided to travel to Europe on my own, which I'm well within my rights to do."

"Without even telli--"

"Yes, without fucking telling you! Like you'd let me go! You don't want me doing *anything*! But here I am! I'm fine, and I'm alive and well, and look at that, I'm not currently being hunted by any law enforcement authority!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And yet, why did you come in the first place? You're framing this as if the situation is concluded, that you're 'alive and well' as some sort of permanent achievement. But when did the trip stop? Why would it not start up again? If you want to be left alone, then the people pestering you need stronger assurances, honey."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"I'm looking for the truth. The truth she's kept me from." Violetta stares at the sky.

"I've told you everything I know!" Magnolia.

"This isn't about *your* cluelessness, you old hag!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Then whose cluelessness is it about?! You're just running the conversation around in circles, tripping up yourself as much as everyone else!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He stamps his cane on the ground.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
"You want the 'truth'? How much has she led you astray? I don't know who to feel worse for when you both so clearly deserve each other." Violetta stares at Magnolia and Viotto in turn.

messages.content:

"Watch your mouth. You weren't raised to behave this way."

messages.content:

"No! Stop being so literal-minded!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"Mourner is a temporary thing, it applies to something you do right after death. It's the noun form of a verb. The whole fuckin' point was this loss being a permanent aspect of her being."

"Clearly the point wasn't conveyed well. That's two against one."

Violetta yells in annoyance.

author.name: scipe
