messages.content:
"H-hey..." 
He follows her out.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
Right outside of the small chamber is a dusty temple-esque structure, and a man Viotto may or may not remember as ‘Solnit’. 

“Good, yes. Just as planned.” He says this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto shields his eyes from something. "Why are there so many people around here that weren't a moment ago?! It's maddening. I can't keep asking for names."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: This is an implicit ask for his name.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Solnit. Don’t waste time introducing yourself, I can actually remember these sorts of things.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Great to hear. Maybe you c-can remember what happened to cause the building to collapse?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “The ship collapsed? Hm. Well, it was one of you three, and I’d place my money on Leocot.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I think you ought to be included on the list of suspects, personally."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I’ve never set foot on there. Feel free to blame me, though.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "On 'there'? We haven't changed locations. Don't try to shirk your responsibility for this."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "It makes you all the more suspicious... evading simple facts."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
He turns to Gratia, who is the other person here. "Is he always this dull?"

"I don't know who the hell either of you are."

Solnit frowns. "Right. Okay. Yes, well done Entenmann. I cleverly fled to this other part of the same ship with no signs of collapse and a completely different structure, which you accessed through the single solitary exit from that small room you were just within. Congratulations on solving the case. Moving on."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You frame moving from one room to another as if it's patently absurd."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "And I generally find that you can't collapse just half of a ship. These things are very structurally interconnected."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "That's strange, then, Viotto, because it does not look like where we are is collapsed to me. It seems rather un-collapsed. Surely that means only half the ship was collapsed?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do you... know what a 'structure' is? You live in a world of magic, and yet you somehow believe all that exists is what you can see with the naked eye? That this room must be sound simply because you can walk within it?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Oh, you do still remember magic exists. I thought you might just be senile, but no, you really are that much of an imbecile."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "All I said was that *you* live in a world of magic. Whether I cohabitate that world with you is entirely another thing."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Regardless, we should get out of here as soon as possible."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Feel free to head the opposite direction of me, destroyer of ships." Solnit walks onward.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto follows.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
Gratia, resigned to the flow of the masses, also follows.

Solnit, without looking back, speaks again. "Dextrum told me you shirked some offer of his after finding out his affiliation with the government. Now, I certainly don't mind inconveniencing the self-important lout. But that reasoning does intrigue me. Do you consider yourself an individualist?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Of course. Man is an island, after all. And it's not as if I pay taxes, so to expect a return on the lack of investment would be narcissistic at best."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I don't think that's the way the idiom typically goes."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Which one?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "That of men and islands. Nothing else you said was a common turn of phrase."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What about them?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "You tend to hear that 'no man is an island'. Though perhaps this differs on Earth."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Maybe so."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Why did you ask?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "It isn't a perspective I get to engage with particularly often."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...you don't... what? How could you not engage with individuals?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I do engage with individuals."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do you purely speak with government representatives?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Much of the time, yes."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ah. That explains it, I suppose."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Good to broaden your horizons, then."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I think everyone in the government should die." Gratia adds this, reminding us that she's here.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That seems a bit murderous."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Who are you, exactly?" Solnit looks perplexed.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gratia." Gratia.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Okay. Doesn't matter. Where was I..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You were in the ship," Viotto offers helpfully.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "No."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Come on. That's a level of denial even you couldn't stoop to. We *met* on the ship."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "The ship we're on right now, you mean? This underground ship we're in?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Sure."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He snorts. "Anyway... you work with beasts, correct?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Animals."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "As I said."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What you said has an odd connotation. I don't understand why you would pick it. I work mainly with domesticated housepets."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Nothing is ever really domesticated."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I suppose, in a metaphysical sense. But if you define an entire term out of existence, then it can only be made useful again by shifting it back. If there is a spectrum of domestication, I work within the latter half of it."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "It's all the same, from my view. They are all rugged individualists in their own right. Merely a trick of the light keeping this fact away from us."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Animals are the opposite of individualists. They cannot exist outside of designated herds, or a human counterpart to replace the herd's role. That is what separates humans from the beasts to begin with."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "No. Some of them maintain a family unit of sorts, but the insertion of humanity makes it clear that most of these structures are formed around our own. There are no animals residing within a society. ...Perhaps ants."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Our own what?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Exactly."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Rats reside within human society. Not just ants. Cockroaches, as well. And many types of birds. Maybe this isn't true where you're from."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “There is a difference between being in a society and being *in* a society.” Solnit holds both hands up, shaking his head.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Oh my goodness you are both insufferable.” Gratia does not enjoy the debate.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Shut up.” Solnit.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do you people just hate reasoned debate? We were getting somewhere."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Yes, exactly. The difference is a relevant one to examine; the physical domain of a society versus the conceptual construct of one.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That's not what we were talking about at all. There are entire human industries revolving around those animals I listed, and entire branches of animal behavior and evolution revolving around those industries. They are exactly as much a part of society as any of us."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Do you just not grasp cause and effect?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Is that it?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “Maybe you’re as integrated into society as a rat, true. But such a definition that equates such a thing universally— it’s a useless one. You may as well define all that exists as part of society the moment a society exists.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "How is what I said the same as circular logic? Society exists because society exists? No, nothing of that sort. We agree human society exists - and if we agree on that, then something functioning on every level of that society must necessarily be part of it, or, on the most basic level, absolutely nothing is."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I can name several levels of society rats do not function in.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do you have some specific tier of society you'd like to name? Is that how it works in your head?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “There are no rats in the clergy.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And society fundamentally cannot exist without a clergy? Very bold of you to say, although I appreciate the support."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I suppose if that's an integral part of your definition, then sure, animals cannot have a social existence."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Are you sure you're being honest, though?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “When did I ever say ‘cannot’?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "We were discussing requirements, not random whims."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I doubt that you would say a human who isn't in the clergy is somehow a lesser part of society. So I was attempting to point out the contradiction. If you merely take issue with a specific rat, then I don't understand the point you're making at all."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “This is a different matter. You implied rats are within every level of society, and I disputed that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No, I did not. You were the one pivoting to rats. I was speaking broadly on animal existence: rats, birds, bugs, anything else I may have listed. And let me be clear - there are absolutely animals involved in religious tradition. Even you wouldn't dare dispute that fact."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Should I be going for simpler examples, for your sake? Perhaps a cow would be better, or a donkey."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “The example isn’t the problem.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Then explain the problem."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “The manner in which humans participate in society is qualitatively different from the way in which animals do so. Even if you decided to count the latter as being ‘in’ society, it would be a definition irrelevant to the actual point.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What is the actual point?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “That animals are not collectivist in nature, bar some debatable specific exceptions.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Neither are humans. Society is born of nurture, not nature. We did not spring into existence desiring a tax form to fill out, as wolves come into existence knowing of the pack they are part of, as ants come into existence knowing their role in the hill, as bees, as tigers, as penguins, as an endless number of things."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Humans are unique in very explicitly *not* knowing our role in life. People may try to tell us otherwise, but God blessed us with that lack of intrinsicness."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "None of us could intuit which berry to pick, which nut to open. We must define the world ourselves. To strip that from us through collectivism is how we return to beast."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “There is a distinction between knowing one’s role in life and being too basal to understand the question.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And what question is that?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “What is one’s role in life.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Gratia is following from a distance so she does not hear either of the other two. The labyrinthine structure does not betray any clear progress, but Solnit seems confident in where he’s heading.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto had forgotten he'd been walking this whole time, honestly. His feet feel light on the ground.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Solnit stops short, holding out an arm to ensure no one goes ahead without him. “…This is it. Apologies, but something needs to be taken care of for us to get out of here.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "And what is that?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“Dealing with a god. Just briefly. Nothing too imposing.”

A vague, guttural noise emanates from the darkened hallway ahead.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Aagh! Why must you continue putting me through these worthless trials!"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He looks around for a corner to cower in.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
Solnit goes Tch. “Hmph. I thought you might be of use, but that’s fine. I shouldn’t need you. It’s just sample retrieval, really, overcomplicated with extra steps…”

Gratia peers into the abyss and gets bored of it.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Have you considered simply *not* dealing with whatever beast this is?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I actually have aspirations and goals, I’m afraid. The aimless conversation is a nice diversion, though.” Solnit prepares some magical nonsense.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
…But is interrupted by a voice shouting “HEY!”

The direction from which the source of the voice is approaching contains a multitude of bizarre looking people, of which Viotto recognizes at least one.

Klaud Reaction.

((End session.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((wow. just FORCING me to recognize a character? intrusive dm...))

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ((Klaud Reaction how could I forget :preview:))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

inlineEmojis.name: preview
inlineEmojis.imageUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\976967131986006106-E7725.png

messages.content: Freed from the tyranny of initiative, Viotto is now running up some stairs.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He trips a few times, but steadies himself and continues upwards.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: The stairwell collapses ahead. His initial trajectory has been blocked, but there are side doors he may use to look for alternate methods of escape.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He tries one to his left.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: By pure coincidence, this is the same way Viotto got here from. He finds himself within the ship… at least, it is kind of recognizable as that material. It’s tilted over onto its side, but very unlike earlier, Viotto is not stuck in a dark collection of rubble. The night sky above is unearthed. Whatever location this vessel has crash landed at, Viotto should be capable of climbing out to there now.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Yes! Ahahaha... away from the dark underbellies of this world. For far too long have I been tied down to this empty labyrinth.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: He climbs out.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: Unfortunately, this is a room that’s part of the fucking stupid puzzle gauntlet from earlier. It happens to have an ambient background that looks like space. Magnolia is here, though. So that’s one familiar face. “Oh.” She looks at you with a mild amount of surprise.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Magnolia! What a pleasant surprise! Please, will you help me out of here?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "I hate these enclosed spaces."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: “…Okay.” She waits more than is polite, but eventually heads over and lends a hand.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He pulls himself up, brushes himself off, and stares directly at her, waiting for her to start moving.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "............................Uh... I dunno. Still makes no damn sense to me where we are, but that 'adversary' guy told me to wait here for you. Threateningly. Threatened me into doing that. Don't know how anyone could've predicted... uh, okay, I know there's at least two people further down, but it seems like whatever was that way isn't interesting, at least to the detective, and the other way is unlocked now..." Magnolia slowly starts walking to the end of the room that's bathed in light.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto follows, not fully having processed what she said just now.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: Detective...?

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: Viotto finds himself, with Magnolia, in a room that resembles an office, albeit one heavily vandalized by graffiti and with its contents knocked all over the place. There are two doors, one he just entered from, and a third humanoid figure beyond him and Magnolia. This person looks vaguely like a demon. Magnolia doesn't have anything in particular to say about this at the moment.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ach! We have entered the abode of something most foul, Magnolia. We have to leave... for, even being in the presence of something seeking out malfeasance is a corruption in itself. Normalization to forces like these must be avoided." He grabs her arm and tries to pull her out, not bothering to look any closer at the figure.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: ((ROLL STRENGTH.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
Viotto has the physical might of a wet noodle, and Magnolia doesn't particularly want to leave. "There's already a lady I know is violently unstable back that way. Better the devil you.... well, I guess that doesn't apply. But I don't see a reason to leave and head back to a dead end."

"No, you should leave." The demon(ess?).

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Reverse psychology, Magnolia! It wants us to contravene the advice of demons and stay. We must leave, as it says."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "...Fucking Virtos." The demon mutters.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Violent instability has its perks. It is obvious. It is undeceptive. It cannot sway you any further, only away from itself, as the horrific front it presents pushes you out."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "We will go. We will deal with it together."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
"I don't have to *deal with--* there's just, there's nothing back there! I mean, if you want to prepare or something, I'd get that, like if you think there's going to be some fight... but we're gonna need to go through here eventually." Magnolia.

"I don't fight." The demon.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That won't work on me, demon. I know your tricks."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "I don't know who you are. One of the TAP people, I suppose...? It matters not." They mutter.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No. I'm not in a position of power over anything."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "I did not claim you were." They point at you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Agh! Get your wretched powers away from me!" He looks around for an alternate exit from the room. A way to 'go through here', as Magnolia said.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: There is another door.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He walks towards it at a normal pace.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
"This is also acceptable." The demon.

Magnolia follows you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: What's on the other side of this metaphorical trench we've passed through?

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
A hallway.

Viotto is interrupted by the end of chapter 15. ((end session))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((intriguing.))

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: Viotto is in a hallway. There’s sounds of commotion further ahead past a turn, and he also just hallucinated maybe?

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Viotto stares into the blank air.
"Ah, Ms. Praxis! How incredible to meet you. I can say that I relate strongly to the struggles you have placed before us today. Inaction, apathy to suffering... these are blights upon our consciousness, a question posed without answer. But there is much to be said about how adherence to magical thinking does the same... we ought to take this up."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: He waits for a response.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: “There’s no one… there.” Magnolia mutters.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Wasn't there, though?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He looks at her with sparkling eyes.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“I don’t know. I feel like I’m losing it…?” She expresses concern, holding her head.

“What do you mean by that?” The voice of the young girl in question sounds from the place Viotto just turned away from.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He turns around calmly. "Losing her mind, I believe. It's an odd turn of phrase. Is letting go of what held you back in the past, your pre-conceptions and grounding, really so bad as losing what makes us human in the first place?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Eulogia Praxis is there. “No, I get why she said that. I meant you.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm not losing my mind. It's rude to say so."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“Ok, so you’re always like this. I get it. It’s like a genie.” She clears her throat. “I was specifically asking about the first set of sentences you spoke when addressing me, about how ‘magical thinking’ can be the same as apathy.”

Magnolia recoils from the inexplicable child.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "In that case, don't you think it's clear? Saying, in your first ever display of power, that NOBODY will have to be alone or in pain... it's the most textbook wishful thinking imaginable. Any promise of perfection may seem effective propaganda at first, but on any small failure, it becomes a *broken* promise. And, may I remind you, your *only* promise, to either keep or break. The moment one person under you experiences anything negative, by their fault or another's, they will cease to think of you as an effective leader. You have driven away everybody who could ever matter, by ignoring every outcome not favorable to you. You are your father with one extra step, and a failed grandiosity. Don't you see?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “No, I just think you’re a pessimist. I’m talking about an endstate, anyway — I fully admit my ideals won’t be enacted immediately.” She rolls her eyes. “I’m also not looking for any kind of support. I’m not a politician.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Everyone is a politician. What would you do against a revolt?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “There wouldn’t be one. And if there was, it wouldn’t matter.” She floats in the air, lying on her front with her hands to her cheeks. The position comes across as incredibly smug. “You weren’t nearly as skeptical with the pope. Isn’t he kind of the same? A lot of generic peace and love talk. Is he an effective leader?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Being 'kind of the same' is applicable to any two things if you stare at them long enough. My key point does not apply to him, and so my criticism fails."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "You say that there wouldn't be a revolt, and in the next word, reason out what would happen in case of a revolt? It's clear that you have doubts. Please, allow us to work through them, before you deliver this ill-advised message to anybody else."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“How the heck would the pope handle a revolt?” She chuckles. “He doesn’t seem to employ an army, and you can’t seriously expect me to believe the old man is hiding immense power by himself.”

She descends back onto her feet. “At any rate, you’ve given me little reason to weigh your words as particularly meaningful.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Why would the pope be revolted against? He hasn't made any promises he can fail to follow through on."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "And, tell me... how do you expect me to prove the meaning behind my words without this conversation continuing?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He steps closer to her.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “No, I get it already. You’re skeptical I can accomplish anything. There’s really nothing left I’m uncertain about.” She backs up in turn. “But you don’t know me, Viotto. You know me even less than her, and she’s basically a stranger to you too.” Eulogia points at Magnolia, who is still here. She doesn’t have much to say at the moment.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You've misinterpreted my statement, deliberately, perhaps? I didn't claim to be skeptical that you could accomplish *anything,* I was skeptical of your claim to be able to accomplish *everything.* You should aim your sights at anything, really."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: There's no conversation opener with Magnolia that Viotto is looking for.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I meant anything of what I had claimed earlier. The act of accomplishment is happening perpetually, in a very silly sense. I’m accomplishing something right now, however useful it may be.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"What you had claimed earlier was an indefinite end to all negative things in life. That's the very issue. Your constituents will not see perpetual 'silly' and 'questionably useful' accomplishment, they will see whether you live up to your words or let them down. What needs change is not your actions, but your messaging. I feel that I've made that clear."
He cocks his head.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Or are you against correcting yourself, for some reason? Do you already believe yourself to be perfect?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I believe I can accomplish what I’ve set my mind to. If I’m perfect is unrelated.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What you've claimed to set your mind to is perfection. Don't be deliberately obtuse."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “So? Deaf men have composed symphonies. The works of one are restricted by only their mind, not their own status.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Which part of you are you comparing to deafness?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Or, have you been reading my lips this entire time?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: She sighs. “I don’t know, Viotto. Maybe you can intuit the answer. You’d empathize well with that hypothetical musician. You might be able to hear, but it seems listening is a struggle.” The unbounded cheshire of this fantasy world grins.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, at the very least you admit to not knowing something. You should display that kind of vulnerability to others, going forward. That can be my final piece of advice."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He shifts his eyes to Magnolia. "Shall we go...?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“Ah, perfect timing. Got someone else to deal with coming, and it would have been rude of me to be the one who forces the conversation to close. You’ve got a knack for abandoning things you started.” The first sign of negativity on a face that has either been overly positive or overconfident shows, and Eulogia turns around, walking to the end of the corridor and taking a right.

“….Uh. Yeah. Let’s just move on.” Magnolia responds after a significant silence.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yes. Let's." He begins walking in the direction Eulogia headed.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
He bumps into a dubiously familiar bird woman (woman who looks like a bird) backing out from the left turn at the end of the corridor. (Incidentally, there is no right path.) 

She swivels around and points an old-timey pistol in Viotto’s face. “Agh!”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto knocks on the wall that Eulogia apparently walked through. Does it sound hollow?

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: The bird is infuriated to have been ignored, but doesn’t fire at this point. The wall does not sound hollow.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Grahhhhh!" Viotto screams and fall backwards performatively, giving credence to what is clearly a prop gun. Making deranged women angry is low on his priority list.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“Who the hell are ye?” The bird asks.

“WHO IS THAT” A voice from a ways away at the hallway to the left yells.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Viotto Entenmann..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He sounds dismayed.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I'm a veterinarian. If you need any assistance."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: “I take offense to that.” The bird woman breathes heavily.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No, I simply meant... I know medicine. As a general concept. We're all made of the same stuff..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "No need to take offense."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“Hmph.”

Magnolia stares at the bird.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Don't be rude, Magnolia."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content:
“Right, uh, sorry.” She holds her other arm with a hand uncomfortably.

“Whatever.” The bird mutters. “If both of you are unarmed, ye should probably stay back.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Why? Is that a threat? If we approach, we ought to be armed, you say. So, we should have been ready for a confrontation? But in that case, why stay so close to the danger? Why not tell us to arm ourselves, or run? You clearly wish to keep us close. Despite us being unacquainted, you have some stake in this, evidently. Or are you merely philanthropic to strangers, that you must monitor us as an authoritarian state would? That's what keeps you going? Disgusting."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Klaud Reaction arrives. (( #viotto-reaction ))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto steps through the door. The exterior looks like it did before he stepped through, that being a hallway. Gratia and Solnit are a bit further ahead.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Why would Sol lie about such a thing...? This is a betrayal, of sorts. Or perhaps the mental space of Eulogia is less complex than one might expect. But we must carry on.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "Wait for me! There's no need to rush this, you know." I hurry after them, trying to see where we're headed in this hallway of deception.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "Power." Solnit addresses Gratia with the end of some exchange before turning back to Viotto. "I can't say for sure how long any of us have, but it feels like denying *any* need to rush would be inaccurate."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, I can't deny your logic, admittedly. But what's your destination here? It feels as if you know more than I do on this."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "I have many irons in the fire, many processes involved in. I am currently attempting to delegate one of them to someone else, because a lot of things are currently ongoing. In terms of physical destination, I only hope to find a more central location from which it is easier to orient ourselves." Solnit manages to avoid any concrete information.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Why do you believe the center of our location would be in this direction, and not any other? Do you have knowledge of our orientation already?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: I cock one of my eyebrows.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "Well, regardless. We should continue."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "Try to get your facts straight next time, though, Sol."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "You're not the only one who knows of power."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
“Intuition, call it. It’s better than staying still. As warped as things have become, getting somewhere does still require going somewhere. That’s a rule that was preserved.”

He starts walking ahead, picking at seemingly random when a crossroads is reached. “I would not consider you someone well versed in the concept of power, Mr. Entenmann.”

“Ugh.” Gratia rolls her eyes and follows him.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: I follow along the branching paths. "Oh? You wouldn't? and yet... our very first interaction was that of me changing your very career trajectory, upsetting Dextrum's opinion of your academic virtues. You will never occupy the position of those lost behind you again, Sol... and that is because of me. I would not demean Entenmann so lightly."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: “Hm. I had forgotten that happened altogether. I suppose I still owe you my thanks for that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yes, yes, of course. You're welcome. Glad to spread awareness."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "And I'm glad you're not too far gone to be beyond self-reflection."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
“Too far gone. Tch. I never thought I was a good fit for that kind of instructive role. I merely have to listen to that man for the time being.”

“You seem like a bad fit for any role that involves interacting with anyone, honestly.” Gratia.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't think that's true, Gratia. For somebody to not be a fit for any type of interaction would render them a non-existence in this world. Even if he cannot be the instructor, he has many options left to him."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "Even he agrees that he must become a listener. Right?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
“Not in whatever way you’re likely implying.” He stops beside a door.

“There’s a lot to life beyond being social. Obviously I’m good at all of it, but y’know. Not like he wouldn’t exist just because he’s a loser.” Gratia.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Everything in life serves social needs. Ceasing to exist is the least of his potential problems. Trust me."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
“How could ceasing to exist being the least of someone’s problems? That’s literally the biggest a problem could be.” Gratia rolls her eyes.

Solnit peers through the doorway. “There’s potentially fates worth than death, I suppose…” He speaks quietly.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Even if there were no such thing as a fate worse than death, that wouldn't negate what I'm saying. If you had to kill two people to stay alive yourself, for example, do you suppose that would be a relatively small issue?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "Do you care for others so little? It's a bit disturbing, honestly."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: I look at her, vaguely disgustedly.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: Oh, a door.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "What's through there?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
“The golem. And others.” Solnit is lost in thought about something.

“Why would I care if I had to kill people to save my own life? It’s literally not even a moral issue at that point.” Gratia scoffs. She then stares at Solnit, curiously.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What's your upper limit? Would you commit genocide to sustain yourself? Omnicide?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "Not a moral issue, you say..."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "I'm a simple man, Gratia. I believe in the sanctity of life, above all else. I merely view life as a function of social communication, rather than a specific biological state. You seem... a little behind even the basic premise, to be honest."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: I turn to Sol. "What others? What golem?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
“I’m ahead of the game. You’ve obviously never had to make a choice like that, old man.”

“Shut up, both of you.” Solnit mutters. He pulls out an oblong object wrapped in cloth and shoves it into Gratia’s hands. “It’s all yours if you pull this off.”

“Yeah, sure. I’m in the middle of owning this guy, though.” She turns back to Viotto. “I mean, I could do the same ridiculous extrapolation. Would you let yourself die to save a horse? A fly? At some point that has to be unsustainable.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"That's specifically why in my hypothetical, it was two people. It's true that there are some grey areas in the middle of the scale - say, sacrificing yourself for somebody younger than you, or one who's more likely to make a difference in the areas that you care about. But if you don't wish to die, it's a basic moral fact that you must also try to create a world where others don't impose unnecessary death upon anyone else, or even themselves."
"No, I would not sacrifice myself for a fly. Because a fly is below me. They feed into the social cycle so, so much less. And so the only way you could justify mass murder is if you believed yourself more important than everyone else. Do you? Do you find life inherently worthless? I don't see why you're doing anything here, in that case. Simply curl up in a ball on the floor and fill your veins with your medicine of choice. I won't look down on you for that."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
Solnit walks away down a different hallway. "I will see you both later. There is something else I need to attend to."

"I'm not going to kill myself because I think my life is valuable. That makes absolutely no sense. Are you senile?" She chuckles. "I'm inherently different from everyone else. Because I'm me. If other people die, that doesn't change my existence. But if I do, that changes everything."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No, I didn't mean a lethal injection. I meant cocaine."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "I'd be happy to bring you food and water for a while, you know."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "If you're such a self essentialist, prove it. Retract into pleasure. It would prove the point to me, at least."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "What is cocaine."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do you know what a recreational drug is?"

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "There are certain substances that exist which, when taken in regularly, automatically make you feel incredibly happy. You can skip the process, is what I'm saying. A shortcut past whatever your purpose here is."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "It's often given to people in their last moments, but that's not a requirement. It can be sustained however long you want."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: "Might've heard something similar. That's not sustainable, though. I'm not the type of person who can afford even simpler pleasures. That's what this is all about." She walks through the door.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, so this is a quest for monetary gain, I see. That's fine enough by me. But please, be open to discussing this again whenever we may get out. I promise I have your best interests in mind, even your inherent differences."

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content: I go in for a hug.

author.name: bloopiero
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\d99c460ae22eacecb7185aae4c31f492-452CA.png

messages.content:
This doesn't work because of the physical distance, but he lightly grazes her shoulder, sure.

The two exit into a larger room one might describe as a "foyer" containing three people, one of which isn't exactly a person but is instead a giant metal humanoid Viotto met one time for some reason, one of which he would recognize as Voreverl Leocot, but not actually Voreverl Leocot rather instead the body that looks completely unlike Voreverl Leocot but claimed to be her on Arctica, and the third of which would take a second to recognize but is obviously just Horatius Kyodu but with shorter hair. However, Viotto has not heard this person identified as Horatius Kyodu because instead for some reason they used the name 'Rowan' when he met them god knows how long ago.

((End session))
